SIMPLE: so-so
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: So-so
<hw>So"-so`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>So</ets> +
<ets>so</ets>.]</ety> <def>Neither very good nor very bad; middling;
passable; tolerable; indifferent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In some Irish houses, where things are <qex>so-so</qex>,⟦br⟧
One gammon of bacon hangs up for a show.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He [Burns] certainly wrote some <qex>so-so</qex> verses to the
Tree of Liberty.</q> <rj><qau>Prof. Wilson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>So-so</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: So-so
<hw>So"-so`</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Tolerably; passably.</def>
<rj><au>H. James.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soss</ent>⟦br⟧
